sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant A as Cacti Node A<br/>(cactus-cmd-api-server)
    participant CA as Consortium Plugin A<br/>(cactus-plugin-consortium-manual)
    participant CB as Consortium Plugin B
    participant B as Cacti Node B<br/>(cactus-cmd-api-server)

    Note over CA,CB: A consortium is a signed list of member nodes —<br/>each entry pairs a public key with a service endpoint.
    A->>CA: getConsortiumJws() / getNodeJws()
    activate CA
    CA-->>A: signed membership (JWS)
    deactivate CA
    A->>B: cross-node request<br/>(carries JWS-authenticated identity)
    activate B
    B->>CB: verify member signature & endpoint
    activate CB
    CB-->>B: member validated
    deactivate CB
    B-->>A: authorized cross-node response
    deactivate B
    Note over A,B: Each node stays sovereign — no shared chain.<br/>Trust is anchored in the consortium membership list.
